(53, 1, 'Absolutely No Sense of Humor', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nUnited States Of America/ English</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n2:30 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Editor</strong><br />\r\nMischa Livingstone</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nErica Russel, Andras Jones, Jessica Livingstone</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Writer</strong><br />\r\nAndras Jones&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nLei Deng</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Music</strong><br />\r\nAndras Jones,&nbsp;Bruce Witkin,&nbsp;Rob Klonel</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nBest Music Video-&nbsp;<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Kolkata Shorts Int. Film Festival-20&#39;,<br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Delhi Shorts International Film Fest-20&#39;</p>', '<p>&#39;Absolutely No Sense Of Humour&#39; MV&nbsp;written and performed by Andras Jones and directed by&nbsp;Mischa Livingstone.</p>', '<p>When ANDRAS JONES played his new song &ldquo;Absolutely No Sense of Humor&rdquo; for his friend Andy Dick, Andy insisted the song was about him. It&#39;s NOT. It&rsquo;s actually a true story about something that happened to Andras at a Radio8Ball show he hosted in Olympia a couple of years ago. But now, because of the video (directed by Mischa Livingstone) it kind of is about Andy.</p>', '<p>The track was engineered and mixed by the great Bruce Witkin (of Hollywood Vampires fame) in just a little more time than it took to write it. About 3 hours. Rob Klonel plays the drums. Bruce is on the bass. The vocal performance is live with Andras playing the Telecaster along with the drummer he&#39;d only met that morning. Toss on a few harmony vocals faster than you cook an egg on a hot pan, and that&#39;s the track before you.</p>', '1628250263-Absolutely No Sense of Humor.jpg', '', '1628597964-Absolutely No Sense of Humor thumbnail.jpg', '1628252984-Absolutely No Sense of Humor 2nd image.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-06 11:44:23', NULL),
(54, 4, 'One Bedroom, One Bath', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nUnited States Of America/ English</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n14 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Writer</strong><br />\r\nMischa Livingstone</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nMischa Livingstone, Julia Brauner, Nicole Bryant, Micaela Hammond&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nCharles Swanson</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Kolkata Shorts Int. Film Festival-20&#39;,<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Delhi Shorts International Film Fest-20&#39;</p>', '<p>A comedy short film written and directed by Mischa Livingstone.</p>', '<p>Our lives are banal and ordinary. Not much happens over the course of any given day. Our problems, big and small, lie in wait for us to give them attention, something we actively avoid doing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So we play with our phones, post cleverly crafted images to social media, look up random facts and places, or read mildly amusing listicles. At some point, though, we&rsquo;re going to have to come out of hiding and face reality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;One Bedroom, One Bath&rdquo; tells the story of two people avoiding their problems. It&rsquo;s a reminder that we all drift, like dust motes caught in a draft, from one moment to the next and often without purpose. Sometimes, we are simply looking to fill time between this and that, momentary distractions to get us from the start of day to its end.</p>', '<p>However, there is poetry to be found in the meaningless moments of our lives. The banal is also beautiful, like the toppings on a hotdog or cloud formations in the sky.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;One Bedroom, One Bath&rdquo; celebrates life&rsquo;s unique ordinariness. It&rsquo;s a reminder that eventually we&rsquo;ll get around to facing those nagging problems that won&rsquo;t leave us alone.</p>', '1628497884-One Bedroom, One Bath main banner.jpg', '', '1628598019-One Bedroom, One Bath thumbnail.png', '1628497884-One Bedroom, One Bath.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-09 08:31:24', NULL),
(55, 4, '2 Minutes', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nFrance/ French</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n2:28 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Producer</strong><br />\r\nMaxence PUPILLO</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Screenplay</strong><br />\r\nJustine BROECKAERT</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nVictor AUBURT</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Editor</strong><br />\r\nVictor DAGAND</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Kolkata Shorts Int. Film Festival-20&#39;,<br />\r\n&#39;Vancouver International Film Festival (Young Festival)&#39;,<br />\r\n&#39;Festival International du Film Tr&egrave;s Court&#39;</p>', '<p>A romantic comedy short film directed by&nbsp;Maxence PUPILLO.</p>', '<p>After he failed his first freediving tournament, Etienne is trying again to win. But this time, a new opponent could change the end of the contest...</p>', '<p>After different experiences on French TV series as an actor, this is Maxence PUPILLO&#39;s first short-movie &ldquo;2 Minutes&rdquo;. The movie has won many prices and has been selected worldwide.</p>', '1628597510-2 minutes banner.jpg', '', '1628597510-2 minutes thumbnail.png', '1628597510-2 MINUTES second picture.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-10 12:11:50', NULL),
(56, 3, 'Libussa Unbound', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nCzech Republic/ Czech, German, English, Hebrew</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n63 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Writer</strong><br />\r\nTaÅ¥&aacute;na Markov&aacute;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nJarmila Pol&aacute;kov&aacute;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nFilm &amp;Sociology</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nDalibor Fencl, Petr Vejsl&iacute;k, Nata&scaron;a Dudinski, TaÅ¥&aacute;na Markov&aacute;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Editor</strong><br />\r\n&Scaron;&aacute;rka Sklen&aacute;Å™ov&aacute;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;8th&nbsp;Indian Cine Filmfest-20&#39;</p>', '<p>A creative documentary directed by&nbsp;TaÅ¥&aacute;na Markov&aacute;.</p>', '<p>Mythical heroine with a thousand faces in the digital age - the legacy of Libussa, an affectionate and wise woman who resolves conflicts peacefully.<br />\r\nHer life is a mystery. Did she ever live? Her story spans countries and centuries. Besides being a Czech national symbol, Libussa is also a heroine of Austrian, German, Italian and American theatre plays and legends, and of a fiction film Pagan Queen by Constantin Werner. The mythical figure of Libussa at times left the world of legends and stepped into the real world.</p>', '<p>Libussa, mythical prophetess who foresaw the glory of Prague, judge and ruler over men, lives a new life in the digital age, thanks to contemporary artists and spiritual seekers. We can meet Libussa as the founder of school of witchcraft and wizardry in Poland, mascot of Czech bronies - fans of My Little Pony series, or contemporary Libussa priestesses. What is it about Libussa that keeps firing up our imagination?</p>', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5zuqnrPYqoI', '1628601254-Libussa Unbound Thumbnail.png', '1628601254-Libussa Unbound 2 image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-10 13:14:14', NULL),
(57, 4, 'Good Night. Sleep tight', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nIndia/ Hindi</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n10:30&nbsp;minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Writer</strong><br />\r\nMihir D Upadhyay</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nMelvika Lobo &amp; Mihir D Upadhyay&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nGolden Medias, Katalyst Creates, Spinoff Entertainment</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nShanti Bhushan Roy</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Editor</strong><br />\r\nHarish Raj &amp; Mahesh Khaire</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Music</strong><br />\r\nAshim Kemson</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;New Delhi Film Festival-18&#39;</p>', '<p>A short film written &amp; directed by&nbsp;Mihir D Upadhyay.</p>', '<p>The film explores a life &amp; stress of a star cop ACP Singh. He is working on a high profile case of serial murderers. Finally he is able to catch them after many months. He returns home for a success dinner with his wife &amp; daughter. He sleeps early tired &amp; relived from the exhausting chase. He is woken up in the middle of the night to find the killers in his house. The go for a full fledged assault on him. He barely manages to survive. He puts a brave fight, injuring himself badly but eventually ends killing them both. He collapses due to exhaustion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When we wakes up he discovers his wife &amp; daughter murdered. He can&#39;t believe his reality. He discovers through a nanny camera installed in his house for the safety of his family, that he had actually killed his family in sleep while visualizing them to be the criminals he had apprehended in the day.</p>', '<p>He has committed what is known as homicidal somnambulism or sleepwalking murder. Sleepwalking murder, is the act of killing someone during an episode of sleepwalking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a very rare but real scenario. The film has been inspired by many such unfortunate events.</p>', '1628772801-banner.png', '', '1628772801-thumbnail.png', '1628772801-2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-12 12:53:21', NULL),
(58, 2, 'The Other Side', '<p><strong>Country</strong><br />\r\nCzech Republic</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n7:39 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director,&nbsp;Writer &amp; Animator</strong><br />\r\nPavel Koutsk&yacute;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nPetr Hor&aacute;k,&nbsp;Dagmar Jur&aacute;kov&aacute;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nAlkay Animation Prague</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nIvan V&iacute;t</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Music</strong><br />\r\nZdenÄ›k ZdenÄ›k</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Kolkata Shorts Int. Film Festival-20&#39;</p>', '<p>An animated short written, directed and animated by&nbsp;Pavel Koutsk&yacute;.</p>', '<p>The film about that the paper has the other side. There takes place an optimistic film about the world full of love and good on the one hand and the pessimistic film about the world of evil, manipulation and violence OTOH.</p>', '<p>But we want to watch only one page of the paper, of course, the better one. So that we stick and attach the paper to the table such a way to be seen only single-sided.</p>', '1628774222-The oher side banner.png', '', '1628774222-The oher side thumbnail.png', '1628774222-The oher side 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-12 13:17:02', NULL),
(59, 3, 'The Angel Of History', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nGermany/ German</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n10:30 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Writer</strong><br />\r\nEric Esser</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nEric Esser</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nMakeShift Movies</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nMichael Zimmer</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Editor</strong><br />\r\nEvelyn Rack</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Music</strong><br />\r\nMatija Strni&scaron;a</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nBest Non-Fiction<br />\r\n&#39;Flensburger Kurzfilmtage&#39;<br />\r\nBest Short Documentary<br />\r\n&#39;Student Short Showcase 2020, Amsterdam&#39;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Kolkata Shorts Int. Film Festival-20&#39;,<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Mumbai Shorts International Film Fest-20&#39;,<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Delhi Shorts International Film Fest-20&#39;</p>', '<p>Original title: &#39;Der Engel der Geschichte&#39;, is a documentary written and directed by&nbsp;Eric Esser.</p>', '<p>A border in Europe. A painting by Paul Klee. A poem by Walter Benjamin. A film about yesterday and today, and how difficult it is to recognize one behind the other.</p>', '<p>There has never been a document of culture, which is not simultaneously one of barbarism.</p>', '1628861729-The Angel of History Banner.png', '', '1628861729-The Angel of History Thumbnail.png', '1628861729-The Angel of History 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-13 13:35:29', NULL),
(60, 4, 'Cubicle', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nUnited States Of America/ English</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n3:18 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Writer</strong><br />\r\nMischa Livingstone</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nMischa Livingstone</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nLei Deng</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Starring</strong><br />\r\nRebecca Lincoln</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Delhi Shorts International Film Fest-20&#39;</p>', '<p>A short film written and directed by Mischa Livingstone.</p>', '<p>Becky Schyster is the best salesperson at BSHR Solutions, with phone skills that are second to none.</p>', '<p>But as she zeros in on the latest sale, her integrity is questioned by the office around her.</p>', '1629116697-Cubicle Banner.png', '', '1629116697-Cubicle thumbnail.png', '1629116697-Cubicle 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-16 12:24:57', NULL),
(61, 3, 'Maman Maman Maman', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nGermany/ English, French</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n37 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Writer</strong><br />\r\nLucia Margarita Bauer</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nAnn Carolin Renninger&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nJoonFilm</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Kolkata Shorts Int. Film Festival-20&#39;,<br />\r\n&#39;IFFR Rotterdam&#39;</p>', '<p>An experimental documentary written and directed by&nbsp;Lucia Margarita Bauer.</p>', '<p>A touching and observant portrait of an annual family gathering and the absurd odyssey the grandmother embarks on after her death.</p>', '<p>Bauer&#39;s quirky family gathers once a year in a French chateau. There is a crooning cousin, family dinners with games and plays, and a great-uncle who still seems to live in the Vichy age. At the heart of this colourful cast is MAMAN, Bauer&#39;s grandmother, who passed away during the shoot. What follows is an increasingly absurd story of a woman who, after her death, embarks on a journey that eventually becomes an odyssey.</p>', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_m6WIhmbAHE', '1629119140-maman maman maman thumbnail.png', '1629119140-maman maman maman 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-16 13:05:40', NULL),
(62, 3, 'Space Cleaners', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nGermany/ English, German</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n23 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director</strong><br />\r\nMarco H&uuml;lser</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nLouis Wick</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nFilmakademie Baden-W&uuml;rttemberg</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nMarcus Ott</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Music</strong><br />\r\nMax Clouth</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Kolkata Shorts Int. Film Festival-20&#39;,</p>', '<p>A documentary directed by&nbsp;Marco H&uuml;lser,</p>', '<p>A look at how scientists in Germany and around the world are trying to get a grip on the problem of space debris, which is threatening everyday life as we know it.</p>', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CQOBab7b43E', '1629199836-Space Cleaners Thumbnail.png', '1629199836-Space cleaners 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-17 11:30:36', NULL),
(63, 2, 'Time O\' The Signs', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nAustria/ English</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n8:36 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Writer</strong><br />\r\nReinhold Bidner</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nGold Extra,&nbsp;Sonja Prlic, Reinhold Bidner</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nGold Extra</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Animation &amp; Editing</strong><br />\r\nReinhold Bidner</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Delhi Shorts International Film Fest-20&#39;</p>', '<p>An experimental animation film directed by&nbsp;Reinhold Bidner.</p>', '<p>&quot;Time o Ì the Signs&quot; is an experimental - narrative but also documentary - animation about digital time thieves of our time, media stupidities and ongoing daily routines. This work wants to question: how do we (not) want to live in a future society?</p>', '<p>Better, faster, more efficient, your faceless shadow in the cloud. Your clock: tick tock, Your stats?<br />\r\nThey drop... The system knows you, better than you do. So you post as a ghost, you stream your dream and you augment life&#39;s content. Say &ldquo;Buy Buy&rdquo; to happiness! A.S.A.P.! C.W.O.T... Machine life balance, apple every day, so smart!<br />\r\nDesigned for the deadline, you resigned from your life, fin(e)?<br />\r\nIn your safe home, immersed in your comfort zone: Time&#39;s up-load? Life filed? All under Control? Or just &quot;Ctrl - alt &ndash; delete&quot;?...</p>', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QbRKvcHh-68', '1629203358-Time of the signs thumbnail.png', '1629203358-Time of the signs 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-17 12:29:18', NULL),
(67, 4, 'Tor', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nTurkey/ Turkish</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n20 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Writer</strong><br />\r\nRAGIP T&Uuml;RK</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nTOLGA KAAN KARASOY&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nFATÄ°H T&Uuml;RKER</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Editor</strong><br />\r\nERHAN &Ouml;RS</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Delhi Shorts International Film Fest-20&#39;</p>', '<p>A short film written and directed by&nbsp;RAGIP T&Uuml;RK.</p>', '<p>Elder AyÅŸe (70) live a difficult life with her grandson. She makes a living by dogsitting of Tor, the guard dog of a neighboring rich family.</p>', '<p>One day, Tor becomes too ill. Family is in abroad and AyÅŸe uses her every means<br />\r\navailable.</p>', '1629379234-Tor banner.png', '', '1629379234-Tor thumbnail.png', '1629379234-Tor 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-19 13:20:34', NULL),
(68, 4, 'Matters Of Time', '<p><strong>Country</strong><br />\r\nNetherlands</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n12:33&nbsp;minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director</strong><br />\r\nThomas Mohr</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nThomas Mohr</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Music</strong><br />\r\nMichael Bonaventure</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Kolkata Shorts Int. Film Festival-20&#39;</p>', '<p>An experimental short film directed by Thomas Mohr.</p>', '<p>From Berlin to Hiroshima, from Hiroshima to Berlin. From Past to Now, from Now to Past. Connecting events, remembering the suffering of war and new beginnings. Observations. 7 identical defined time units each containing a series of 24 progressing intervals of shifting box systems descending from 25x25=625 to 2x2=4 images. The construction of each unit is exactly the same, the content of each unit is entirely individual.</p>', '<p>Walking through a winter night in Berlin, going from Miyajima island to Hiroshima, the experience of My Facebook Timeline Having devastating destruction in mind and reconstruction. Straight forward, up side down, rotating. Positive, negative. Complex layers, more complex layers. Text, subtext.</p>', '1629465414-MOT banner.png', '', '1629465414-MOT thumbnail.png', '1629465414-MOT 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-20 09:56:11', NULL),
(69, 4, 'Die Schwingen des Geistes', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nAustria/ German</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n29 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Writer</strong><br />\r\nAlbert Meisl</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nLena Weiss</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nFilmakademie Wien</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nAlexander Dirninger</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Editing</strong><br />\r\nSebastian Schreiner</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Delhi Shorts International Film Fest-20&#39;</p>', '<p>A comedy short film directed by&nbsp;Albert Meisl.</p>', '<p>The failed Viennese musicologist Szabo works as an animal carer and house sitter for wealthy people. But when visited by his successful, younger ex-colleague Fitzthum, a rare parrot, which he should guard, escapes him.</p>', '<p>Szabo sees his already precarious life in shambles, but Fitzthum has a brilliant idea and together they go out in search of a look-alike of the precious animal.</p>', '1629465511-Wings of spirit banner.png', '', '1629465511-Wings of spirit thumbnail.png', '1629465511-Wings of spirit 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-20 10:31:54', NULL),
(70, 4, 'The Death of Marie', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nUnited States Of America/ English</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n14 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Writer</strong><br />\r\nSiggi Kjartan</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nSara Nassim,&nbsp;Lilja Baldurs</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nRaven Collective</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nShadi Chaaban</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Music</strong><br />\r\nBjarni Frimann</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Delhi Shorts International Film Fest-20&#39;</p>', '<p>A short drama film written and directed by&nbsp;Siggi Kjartan.</p>', '<p>Forty-eight years after Marie&#39;s heart stopped beating, she learns she is about to die.</p>', '<p>The young Nico, Marie&#39;s young granddaughter, is subsequently exposed to the darker sides of her family.</p>', '1629465575-The death of marie banner.png', '', '1629465575-The death of marie thumbnail.png', '1629465575-The death of marie 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-20 10:57:55', NULL),
(71, 3, 'A Lâ€™usage Des Vivants', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nBelgium/ French</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n26:46&nbsp;minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Editor</strong><br />\r\nPauline Fonsny</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Writers</strong><br />\r\nPauline Fonsny,&nbsp;Maia Chauvrier, Semira Adami</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nAlice Lemaire</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nContre-Ciels, Atelier Cin&eacute;ma</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nPierre de Wurstemberger, Lou Vernin, Pauline Fonsny</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Delhi Shorts International Film Fest-20&#39;</p>', '<p>A social&nbsp;documentary written and directed by&nbsp;Pauline Fonsny.</p>', '<p>In 1998, Semira Adamu, a 20 year-old, so-called &ldquo;illegal&rdquo;, Nigerian immigrant on Belgian soil, was smothered to death by a police cushion as they attempted to evict her. 20 years later, in a combined female war cry, two women tell her story.</p>', '<p>Through their tales, they highlight the reality of detention centers intended for migrant people, the conditions of such imprisonment, the suffering of detainees, the abuse of guards and policemen.</p>', '1629465634-To the living banner.png', '', '1629465634-To the living thumbnail.png', '1629465634-To the living 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-20 12:07:02', NULL),
(72, 4, 'Huaca', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nEcuador/ Spanish</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n14:45&nbsp;minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Writer</strong><br />\r\nDiego Ortu&ntilde;o</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nMichelle Echeverr&iacute;a&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nDominio Digital</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nT&uacute;pac Galarza</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Editor</strong><br />\r\nPaula Vera</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Delhi Shorts International Film Fest-20&#39;</p>', '<p>A suspense-horror short film written and directed by&nbsp;Diego Ortu&ntilde;o.</p>', '<p>HUACA is a fiction short film that tells a story inspired by the legends of Huacas in the Ecuadorian highlands. It&nbsp;rescues aspects of the Andean culture and the Ecuadorian moorland: the field, the mixture of languages, the ancient chants and the ability to generate stories that seek an explanation in the supernatural.</p>', '<p>It is a production that translates, into a more current language, the horror stories that have been circulating for generations around the country.</p>', '1629465720-Huaca banner.png', '', '1629465720-Huaca thumbnail.png', '1629465720-Huaca 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-20 12:45:14', NULL),
(73, 4, 'Tiffin', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nIndia/ Hindi</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n10:6&nbsp;minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Writer</strong><br />\r\nTalat Shakeel&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nGhania&nbsp;Siddique</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nAshique Saira Shahir, Faisal Saleem</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Editor</strong><br />\r\nGhania&nbsp;Siddique</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Kolkata Shorts Int. Film Festival-20&#39;</p>', '<p>A children&#39;s short film written and directed by&nbsp;Talat Shakeel.</p>', '<p>A muslim girl, Fatima,&nbsp;is inseparable from her friends in school. But the dynamic changes during lunchbreak&nbsp;as&nbsp;her friends share lunchboxes freely with each other but refuse to share food with her.</p>', '<p>As she becomes more aware of the reasons for her ostracization and feels alienated,&nbsp;an empty lunchbox inspires hope in her life.</p>', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Sw626t0accU', '1629643351-Tiffin thumbnail.png', '1629643351-Tiffin 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-22 12:28:29', NULL),
(74, 3, 'Naaz Hotel', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nIndia/ Urdu, Hindi</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n22:50 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director</strong><br />\r\nYusra Hasan</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nYusra Hasan,&nbsp;Muntaha Amin,&nbsp;Tulika Kumari,&nbsp;Asiya Naqvi,&nbsp;Talat Shakeel,&nbsp;Ghania&nbsp;Siddique</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nGhania&nbsp;Siddique</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nSpecial Mention Award-<br />\r\nCut in Student film festival, TISS Mumbai<br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;9th&nbsp;Kolkata Shorts Int. Film Festival-20&#39;</p>', '<p>A documented memoir directed by&nbsp;Yusra Hasan.</p>', '<p>A short documentary about a third-generation Muslim Woman, who unwittingly rediscovers her relationship with her grandfather as she traces the history of their family&nbsp;hotel-&nbsp;Naaz&nbsp;Hotel&nbsp;and Purani Dilli.</p>', '<p>The film has been made by 6 women and produced by AJK MRC, Jamia Millia Islamia, New Delhi. It&#39;s been shot on Canon 5D Mark 4 and Sony F5.</p>', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ggMmQSLqWbw', '1629643460-Naaz Hotel thumbnail.png', '1629643460-Hotel Naaz 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-22 12:56:12', NULL),
(75, 5, 'Extreme Number', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nGermany/ Russian-German</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n81 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director &amp; Writer</strong><br />\r\nIrina Arms</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nJochen Arms, Irina Arms</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nArms&nbsp;Filmproduktion GmbH</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nSven Jakob-Engelmann</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Editor</strong><br />\r\nLaia Prat, Marta Malowanczyk</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;8th Indian Cine Film Festival-20&#39;,<br />\r\n&#39;8th Noida International Film Festival-21&#39;</p>', '<p>A feature drama film written and directed by&nbsp;Irina Arms.</p>', '<p>The story tells of a young refugee from Chechnya who comes to Germany and is thrown into prison in Berlin. He falls in love with a girl who translates for him, and enlists her help for him to flee. He then joins a terrorist group in Berlin that gives him the order to attack the Russian embassy.</p>', '<p>Authentic war documentation is embedded in the film as the Chechen protagonist`s flashbacks. This is real coverage of war, shot by a Chechen rebel 1994 &ndash; 2000 in Chechnya. Real and fictional levels of the story blend together as a whole.</p>', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HP9Le0nPCOA', '1629643513-Extreme Number thumbnail.png', '1629643513-Extreme Number 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-22 13:35:59', NULL),
(76, 5, 'Daria', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nCzech Republic/ Czech</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n89 minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director</strong><br />\r\nMatÄ›j Pichler</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nMichal Theer, Patrik Kettner</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nEurope DMT Production</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nAle&scaron; Hart</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Writer</strong><br />\r\nDaniel MiÅˆovsk&yacute;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nBest Feature<br />\r\n&#39;Berlin Flash Film Festival 2021&#39;<br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;8th&nbsp;Indian Cine Film Festival-20&#39;</p>', '<p>A mysterious thriller feature film directed by&nbsp;MatÄ›j Pichler.</p>', '<p>When Daria disappears after their first date, Marek finds her in a psychiatric hospital. Everything might be part of a disturbing game played by powerful pharmaceutical companies, though the truth may be more frightening than either of them realize.</p>', '<p>Mysterious, artistically stylised thriller about the thin line between reality and fiction madness and normalcy, suggestion and manipulation, but also about fear and courage. Reflection of current problems and the inevitability of the influence of the powerful. Can people still control their lives today, or has freedom never been so vague?</p>', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A0LpPS4I5ys', '1629643587-Daria thumbnail.png', '1629643587-Daria 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-22 14:16:27', NULL),
(77, 5, 'Women At The Peak', '<p><strong>Country/ Language</strong><br />\r\nCzech Republic/ Czech</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong><br />\r\n107&nbsp;minutes</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director</strong><br />\r\nLenka Kny</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Writers</strong><br />\r\nHana Cielov&aacute;,&nbsp;Nora K.,&nbsp;Lenka Kny</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Producers</strong><br />\r\nPalo Jelenek,&nbsp;Lenka Kny,&nbsp;Igor Rattaj</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production Company</strong><br />\r\nBlue Time</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Director of Photography</strong><br />\r\nMichael Baumbruck</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Editor</strong><br />\r\nAlois Fis&aacute;rek</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Awards</strong><br />\r\nOfficial Selection-<br />\r\n&#39;8th&nbsp;Indian Cine Film Festival-20&#39;</p>', '<p>A romantic comedy feature film directed by Lenka Kny.</p>', '<p>Helena, a bit quirky single mother and owner of a bio caf&eacute;, is weary of her partner&#39;s promises of spending Christmas with her and their 8-year-old son Mikul&aacute;&scaron;. Prompted by her aunt Ela, Helena with Mikul&aacute;&scaron; leave Prague to spend Christmas in the mountains.&nbsp;Due to her own absent-mindedness and a twist of fate, she finds herself instead of a luxurious hotel in a mountain cottage called Loneliness, where mountaineer Richard practices adrenaline sports.</p>', '<p>The loner lives with his little daughter Zuza and a very sociable brother Mi&scaron;o. And unsuspecting Helena doesn Ìt know yet about her loving mother Ìs plan to make her disapproving father join Helena in the mountain resort too. It&#39;s Christmas time and family should be together!</p>', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zfmEQF71yFI', '1629986419-Women at the Peak thumbnail.png', '1629986419-Women at the Peak 2nd image.png', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '2021-08-26 13:51:21', NULL);

